Are you?

711
00:43:23,327 --> 00:43:26,288
I told you I'd take care of you, didn't I?

712
00:43:26,455 --> 00:43:28,540
It's like proper...

713
00:43:32,085 --> 00:43:34,421
-I'm loving this, Alfie. It's so me.
-Good.

714
00:43:34,588 --> 00:43:35,964
-That's the Albert Bridge, there.
-Yeah.

715
00:43:36,048 --> 00:43:38,091
And that's the Tower there.
Harrods is up there.

716
00:43:38,217 --> 00:43:40,552
-And you got me all that silk underwear.
-Yeah.

717
00:43:40,594 --> 00:43:42,262
There you are.

718
00:43:42,387 --> 00:43:44,014
-I told you I'd take care of...
-It cost you so much.

719
00:43:44,181 --> 00:43:46,683
Well, what's money? It doesn't matter.

720
00:44:08,664 --> 00:44:10,082
-Alfie?
-Yeah.

721
00:44:10,666 --> 00:44:13,043
-What do you think?
-Wow. That looks amazing.

722
00:44:13,168 --> 00:44:15,170
-You like it?
-Yeah, it's beautiful.

723
00:44:16,004 --> 00:44:18,715
The silk feels so good on my skin.

724
00:44:18,841 --> 00:44:22,177
It's a shame they haven't brought the bed,
isn't it? Sorry about that.

725
00:44:22,219 --> 00:44:23,846
-We don't need a bed.
-No?

726
00:44:23,846 --> 00:44:26,557
We could just do it here.

727
00:44:26,598 --> 00:44:28,851
-I've done it on a hardwood floor.
-You have?

728
00:44:28,976 --> 00:44:31,895
-Marble, even.
-It's a bit uncomfortable, isn't it?

729
00:44:32,646 --> 00:44:33,981
Wait, look.

730
00:44:35,983 --> 00:44:37,609
Just lay out the fox.

731
00:44:37,693 --> 00:44:39,069
-Be nice.
-Okay, well...

732
00:44:39,153 --> 00:44:41,155
-Cozy, like that.
-Yeah.

733
00:44:42,698 --> 00:44:45,993
-Come on.
-I just need a few more minutes, that's all.

734
00:44:47,786 --> 00:44:48,871
Why?

735
00:44:49,746 --> 00:44:55,502
Just to savor the moment
of looking at you, that's all.

736
00:45:02,801 --> 00:45:06,430
Was you serious when you said
you liked how that bracelet looked on me?

737
00:45:07,181 --> 00:45:08,348
Just now, at Cartier?

738
00:45:09,349 --> 00:45:15,647
'Cause you said if I really felt like
I couldn't live without it...

739
00:45:16,190 --> 00:45:18,942
And you've decided you can't live without it.

740
00:45:26,408 --> 00:45:27,993
Three more minutes.

741
00:45:30,204 --> 00:45:32,998
I've got such a crush on my boss.

742
00:45:33,040 --> 00:45:34,583
I know he's married. I'm married.

743
00:45:34,625 --> 00:45:37,294
But honestly, if he asked me
to run off with him tomorrow,

744
00:45:37,377 --> 00:45:40,214
I'd have to take a long, hard look at my life.

745
00:45:40,255 --> 00:45:42,799
Not that he necessarily shares
the same feelings.

746
00:45:42,966 --> 00:45:46,303
-Does he know your feelings?
-He knows I'm fond of him.

747
00:45:47,429 --> 00:45:49,640
He did take me to the opera one night.

748
00:45:49,806 --> 00:45:52,226
God, listen to me.
I sound like a crazy person.

749
00:45:53,477 --> 00:45:56,271
-You're the wrong person to ask.
-Ask what?

750
00:45:57,397 --> 00:46:02,152
I was going to take you out for a drink
and ask you to start a new gallery with me.

751
00:46:03,445 --> 00:46:06,949
Are you joking? Our own business?
That's my dream.

752
00:46:06,990 --> 00:46:10,202
Listen, a number of clients and artists
would dump Lois Geller in a heartbeat

753
00:46:10,285 --> 00:46:11,328
and come with me.

754
00:46:11,453 --> 00:46:13,747
And you have such a good eye
for the new painters.

755
00:46:13,914 --> 00:46:17,918
I mean, yes, it's expensive,
but if we each raise half the money...

756
00:46:19,253 --> 00:46:20,838
I just can't believe this.

757
00:46:20,963 --> 00:46:22,548
The timing's right.

758
00:46:33,308 --> 00:46:36,061
Can you believe he wound up
with that hot little wet dream?

759
00:46:36,103 --> 00:46:39,648
She's unbelievable. Look. Look.
Whatever it costs him, it's worth it.

760
00:46:39,731 --> 00:46:42,568
That body. I bet she's an acrobat.

761
00:46:43,652 --> 00:46:47,698
I'll bet she knows a few tricks.
I wonder if she plays around?

762
00:46:47,698 --> 00:46:49,324
I got to find out.

763
00:46:49,867 --> 00:46:51,702
-No.
-Life's a risk, boys.

764
00:46:51,743 --> 00:46:53,829
You going to pump iron, then?

765
00:46:53,954 --> 00:46:56,248
No. She's out of your league, man.
Don't you...

766
00:46:56,373 --> 00:46:58,250
-You gonna?
-Yeah.

767
00:46:58,250 --> 00:46:59,877
If you don't, I will.

768
00:47:01,461 --> 00:47:05,841
I think I prefer this one, just slightly.
The brightness.

769
00:47:05,841 --> 00:47:08,844
Yeah. Didn't he say that he wanted me
to include this one, too?

770
00:47:09,011 --> 00:47:12,014
Yeah, definitely. Let's not forget this.
This is brilliant.

771
00:47:12,139 --> 00:47:14,266
I mean, the blue, it's just...

772
00:47:15,058 --> 00:47:18,312
And side by side, I think.
They'll be really good side by side.

773
00:47:18,395 --> 00:47:20,522
Do you want a drink? Tea or water?

774
00:47:20,564 --> 00:47:22,649
Tea is lovely, thank you.

775
00:47:23,650 --> 00:47:26,320
I told you he'd do a great job
of promoting you.

776
00:47:26,320 --> 00:47:27,488
He's a dynamo.

777
00:47:27,488 --> 00:47:29,406
He thinks the world of you.

778
00:47:29,406 --> 00:47:32,826
Really? Why? Did he say something?

779
00:47:33,410 --> 00:47:36,747
Well, he obviously has enormous respect
for yourjudgment,

780
00:47:36,830 --> 00:47:38,832
and supposedly a total dependency

781
00:47:38,957 --> 00:47:41,084
on the chocolate truffles
you turned him on to.

782
00:47:43,003 --> 00:47:46,840
Yeah, it's funny. I have a confession.

783
00:47:48,509 --> 00:47:51,053
I've come to the conclusion that...

784
00:47:54,848 --> 00:47:56,099
Have you...

785
00:47:56,934 --> 00:47:58,602
Have you always had those earrings?

786
00:47:58,685 --> 00:48:02,898
These pearls? No, they're new.

787
00:48:05,317 --> 00:48:06,527
Where did you get them?

788
00:48:06,902 --> 00:48:08,153
They were a gift.

789
00:48:09,321 --> 00:48:10,322
A gift.

790
00:48:10,948 --> 00:48:14,952
All right, you have to promise
that you won't tell anybody, okay?

791
00:48:14,952 --> 00:48:18,163
They're from Greg.

792
00:48:20,582 --> 00:48:21,667
What?

793
00:48:22,334 --> 00:48:24,336
Yeah, they're from Greg.

794
00:48:25,337 --> 00:48:27,297
I shouldn't even be blabbing about this,

795
00:48:29,633 --> 00:48:33,470
but we've kind of been having
a little something together.

796
00:48:34,012 --> 00:48:35,055
A what?

797
00:48:37,057 --> 00:48:38,267
An affair.

798
00:48:39,351 --> 00:48:42,479
It sounds so dramatic, doesn't it?
But that's what it is.

799
00:48:42,521 --> 00:48:45,065
We've been having an affair.

800
00:48:45,858 --> 00:48:48,485
Please, don't look so shell-shocked. Don't.

801
00:48:48,527 --> 00:48:49,820
He's married.

802
00:48:49,862 --> 00:48:52,030
Yeah, but we all know
what a shambles that is,

803
00:48:52,156 --> 00:48:53,824
and it's not because of me.

804
00:48:53,949 --> 00:48:57,494
I don't know, it just all got very serious,
very quickly.

805
00:48:57,578 --> 00:48:58,620
Since when?

806
00:48:58,620 --> 00:49:02,541
For a while now. At first, we just met
and we talked about my work.

807
00:49:03,917 --> 00:49:06,295
He is so perceptive. And then he told me...

808
00:49:07,004 --> 00:49:09,548
He told me I wandered into his dream,

809
00:49:10,215 --> 00:49:11,550
and he put his hand on mine

810
00:49:11,633 --> 00:49:13,927
and told me how miserable he was at home

811
00:49:14,052 --> 00:49:17,472
and, well, things just went from there.

812
00:49:18,515 --> 00:49:20,267
He's a fabulous lover, and...

813
00:49:22,019 --> 00:49:23,896
I just don't know.
I don't want him to leave his wife for me,

814
00:49:23,937 --> 00:49:25,856
and he was going to do that already.

815
00:49:28,525 --> 00:49:32,571
I don't know, it feels like I'm in a soap opera,
but it's so lovely.

816
00:49:32,905 --> 00:49:34,948
But I don't know if it's just a reaction,

817
00:49:34,948 --> 00:49:38,869
you know, after spending six years
with a wife that's bipolar.

818
00:49:39,453 --> 00:49:40,954
I don't know.

819
00:49:42,539 --> 00:49:43,749
Are you okay?

820
00:49:45,834 --> 00:49:48,795
Will you please not leave
your bicycle in the hallway?

821
00:49:48,837 --> 00:49:50,631
I nearly broke my neck.

822
00:49:51,048 --> 00:49:54,218
-What's the matter?
-Nothing. Did you hear anything?

823
00:49:54,218 --> 00:49:55,219
About?

824
00:49:55,219 --> 00:49:58,138
What the hell do you think about?
Your book!

825
00:49:58,180 --> 00:50:01,475
Hey, back off! What is eating you?

826
00:50:01,558 --> 00:50:05,270
I've been by the goddamned phone all day!
What's the problem?

827
00:50:05,521 --> 00:50:09,525
I can't stand working for Greg Clemente!
He treats me like a fucking secretary!

828
00:50:09,525 --> 00:50:13,570
Book his tables, get his lunches,
arrange his theater tickets!

829
00:50:13,654 --> 00:50:15,948
I need my own gallery!

830
00:50:17,491 --> 00:50:19,660
I've got a headache. My head is splitting!

831
00:50:19,785 --> 00:50:21,161
Take your pills.

832
00:50:21,245 --> 00:50:24,331
What the hell do you think
I'm trying to do here?

833
00:50:25,123 --> 00:50:26,917
Where are they? Excuse me.

834
00:50:27,042 --> 00:50:29,419
I thought you liked working for him.

835
00:50:30,254 --> 00:50:32,381
I need to start a family!

836
00:50:33,674 --> 00:50:37,594
You know, I wouldn't have to be doing this
if you could just support us.

837
00:50:37,719 --> 00:50:40,138
You know what? You've had trouble
on your last three jobs.

838
00:50:40,138 --> 00:50:41,765
Maybe it's not always your employers.

839
00:50:41,890 --> 00:50:44,685
Yeah? What the hell
is that supposed to mean?

840
00:50:44,852 --> 00:50:46,937
Look, start your own art gallery!

841
00:50:47,729 --> 00:50:49,314
And with what?

842
00:50:49,314 --> 00:50:51,316
We can't afford to
pay the food and rent around here

843
00:50:51,358 --> 00:50:52,401
without my mother helping!

844
00:50:52,484 --> 00:50:55,571
Hey, you have a migraine!
Don't take it out on me!

845
00:51:01,201 --> 00:51:02,244
Hello.

846
00:51:02,578 --> 00:51:04,580
Roy? Malcolm Dodds.

847
00:51:05,789 --> 00:51:06,957
Hello.

848
00:51:07,040 --> 00:51:11,044
Hi. Look, we are so sorry that
we've held you up for so long on this book.

849
00:51:11,044 --> 00:51:13,589
But there's been a lot of talk about it up here,

850
00:51:13,589 --> 00:51:18,051
and we've decided
it's not going to work for us.

851
00:51:20,137 --> 00:51:21,096
And?

852
00:51:21,471 --> 00:51:23,432
I mean, obviously, we liked it.

853
00:51:23,515 --> 00:51:26,476
But it's not that different
to something else we're going to publish,

854
00:51:26,476 --> 00:51:29,062
and we didn't want two books
with the same idea.

855
00:51:29,521 --> 00:51:30,689
I see.

856
00:51:34,693 --> 00:51:36,820
But in the end, you preferred the other one.

857
00:51:36,987 --> 00:51:40,782
To be perfectly frank, Roy,
there are nice moments in it.

858
00:51:40,782 --> 00:51:44,453
But a lot of people here
didn't think it was your best work.

859
00:51:44,578 --> 00:51:46,622
Anyway, I hope you're going to try us again.

860
00:51:47,289 --> 00:51:49,249
What if I can rewrite it?

861
00:51:51,293 --> 00:51:52,461
Am I disturbing you?

862
00:51:52,503 --> 00:51:54,880
Mum, can't you call sometimes
before you come over?

863
00:51:55,047 --> 00:51:56,507
I've got a horrible headache.

864
00:51:56,590 --> 00:51:59,343
-Migraines are tension, darling.
-Yes, I know what migraines are!

865
00:51:59,343 --> 00:52:02,137
And I need to change my life.

866
00:52:02,262 --> 00:52:05,098
You shouldn't be working.
You should be raising a family.

867
00:52:05,182 --> 00:52:07,392
I really don't want
to discuss this right now, Mum.

868
00:52:07,476 --> 00:52:09,728
Well, I've come to share
an incredible insight.

869
00:52:09,812 --> 00:52:12,981
I've spent two hours with Cristal Delgiorno,
two riveting hours.

870
00:52:12,981 --> 00:52:14,149
I'm not in the mood.

871
00:52:14,191 --> 00:52:16,777
I'm just not in the mood
to get into any of that right now.

872
00:52:16,985 --> 00:52:17,820
Can I help myself to a drink?

873
00:52:17,903 --> 00:52:19,613
For some reason,
I love your brand of whiskey.

874
00:52:19,655 --> 00:52:21,031
I'm not normally a whiskey drinker.

875
00:52:21,198 --> 00:52:23,617
Well, that's it. They rejected my novel.

876
00:52:23,784 --> 00:52:25,828
-Roy.
-They don't think it comes off.

877
00:52:25,994 --> 00:52:28,163
Not my best work, try harder.

878
00:52:28,622 --> 00:52:31,208
After all this time,
leaving you dangling like that.

879
00:52:31,250 --> 00:52:33,794
I can't try harder. That's all I have in me.

880
00:52:33,877 --> 00:52:36,547
You gave them sections to read.
They seemed okay with it.

881
00:52:36,672 --> 00:52:39,258
They seemed to like sections,
but the whole book...

882
00:52:39,341 --> 00:52:41,510
-Can I tell you an insight?
-What? What is it?

883
00:52:41,635 --> 00:52:44,346
Well, I know
you're going to pooh-pooh this, Roy,

884
00:52:44,346 --> 00:52:45,681
being so scientific minded,

885
00:52:45,806 --> 00:52:49,059
but it turns out that I've lived before.

886
00:52:49,142 --> 00:52:50,686
No. No, Mother!

887
00:52:50,686 --> 00:52:53,981
No, I've existed before in other incarnations!
Cristal is certain of it.

888
00:52:54,022 --> 00:52:56,692
Look, Helena, I'm not in the mood
for that crap right now, okay?

889
00:52:56,775 --> 00:52:57,901
-No, no, no. I'm not.
-But...

890
00:52:57,985 --> 00:53:01,321
But you will be in the mood
when you realize the importance of that fact.

891
00:53:01,405 --> 00:53:03,574
If it's so for me, it's so for everyone.
You, as well.

892
00:53:03,615 --> 00:53:05,200
Make her shut up, Sally. I'm going to kill her.

893
00:53:05,284 --> 00:53:09,163
Please, let's not get ugly here.
Mum, he just got some really bad news.

894
00:53:09,246 --> 00:53:13,000
If you mean the rejection of that silly book,
I tried to prepare you for it.

895
00:53:13,000 --> 00:53:14,001
Cristal predicted it.

896
00:53:14,084 --> 00:53:15,711
I was sure the book came off fine.

897
00:53:15,794 --> 00:53:17,296
Am I that blind about my own work?

898
00:53:17,421 --> 00:53:20,257
Cristal says your future is not in the arts.

899
00:53:20,340 --> 00:53:22,134
I'm telling you, Sally,
get her out of here! Out!

900
00:53:22,301 --> 00:53:25,888
Well, what's wrong with medicine?
You have the education.

901
00:53:26,013 --> 00:53:29,349
If writing is not in your future,
medicine is a noble way to earn a living.

902
00:53:29,349 --> 00:53:31,185
Okay, all right... Are you thick?

903
00:53:31,351 --> 00:53:34,563
I am never going to be a doctor, okay?
That boat sailed years ago, okay?

904
00:53:34,646 --> 00:53:38,650
You got it? Maybe I'll be
a chauffeur or a messenger.

905
00:53:38,650 --> 00:53:41,403
So, your daughter married badly.
Now can you get the hell out?

906
00:53:41,403 --> 00:53:45,449
How can you ask her to get out
when she is the one paying the rent?

907
00:53:45,449 --> 00:53:47,993
I'm sick of hearing that. She'll get it back,
she'll get all the money back!

908
00:53:48,160 --> 00:53:49,786
How will she get it back?

909
00:53:49,828 --> 00:53:51,413
What are you gonna do, rob a bank?

910
00:53:51,497 --> 00:53:55,250
I am sick and tired of sitting around,
watching my life evaporate,

911
00:53:55,334 --> 00:53:56,919
while you keep trying to prove a point!

912
00:53:57,085 --> 00:53:59,880
It's all futile. Cristal said it's not his moment.

913
00:53:59,880 --> 00:54:02,633
Arcadia was the only one interested,
but they're knowledgeable men,

914
00:54:02,716 --> 00:54:04,051
so I guess it doesn't come off!

915
00:54:04,218 --> 00:54:07,387
Cristal was right! I have to face it!
I was a one-book fluke!

916
00:54:07,513 --> 00:54:09,890
Cristal said at some point,
in the distant future.

917
00:54:10,015 --> 00:54:11,350
Maybe she was talking about another life.

918
00:54:11,391 --> 00:54:16,146
Mother! Will you be still?
You drink and chatter incessantly!

919
00:54:16,605 --> 00:54:18,148
Christ, my head is killing me.

920
00:54:18,232 --> 00:54:22,027
I drank a little, yes,
to celebrate the miraculous!

921
00:54:22,027 --> 00:54:23,195
Is that so terrible?

922
00:54:23,320 --> 00:54:25,614
That I come here with great news,

923
00:54:25,697 --> 00:54:29,952
news that renders all this futile
in the grand scheme of things.

924
00:54:29,993 --> 00:54:33,205
I mean, I'm saying we don't only live once.

925
00:54:33,288 --> 00:54:35,415
We live over and over again.

926
00:54:36,208 --> 00:54:39,169
Cristal says I existed in Elizabethan England.

927
00:54:39,753 --> 00:54:43,507
All I'm saying is there's hope,
hope that maybe Roy will write another book,

928
00:54:43,549 --> 00:54:45,717
but in some future incarnation.

929
00:54:50,806 --> 00:54:52,975
I've got to get out of here!

930
00:54:55,602 --> 00:55:00,858
Oh, God. I can't do it anymore.
I can't be in this marriage.

931
00:55:00,983 --> 00:55:03,360
Let him go. Let him go. Let him go.

932
00:55:03,402 --> 00:55:05,404
You can do so much better.

933
00:55:05,696 --> 00:55:07,614
You know, Cristal says that
that man you work for,

934
00:55:07,614 --> 00:55:11,952
the one you're always so high on.
She says don't rule him out.

935
00:55:18,000 --> 00:55:21,503
At that moment,
with his life going down the drain,

936
00:55:21,503 --> 00:55:23,881
Roy only wanted to see Dia.

937
00:55:26,717 --> 00:55:28,886
And, suddenly, there she was.

938
00:55:42,941 --> 00:55:46,236
But even if she wasn't getting married,
what the hell chance did he have?

939
00:55:46,612 --> 00:55:49,114
What could he offer her? What was he?

940
00:55:49,198 --> 00:55:53,660
A washed-up writer at 38?
A member of the "formerly promising" club?

941
00:55:54,203 --> 00:55:58,373
"Royal Channing." A hell of a name
for a limo driver or a bike messenger.

942
00:55:58,749 --> 00:56:01,835
The thought of beginning a new book
paralyzed him.

943
00:56:01,877 --> 00:56:03,712
He'd lost all his nerve.

944
00:56:04,129 --> 00:56:07,591
And what was he supposed to do,
work days and write nights?

945
00:56:07,716 --> 00:56:10,385
Not that he had an idea for another book.

946
00:56:10,552 --> 00:56:14,640
And just when you think
things can't possibly get any worse,

947
00:56:14,765 --> 00:56:18,185
fate lets you know
there's bigger trouble out there.

948
00:56:23,732 --> 00:56:24,817
Hello.

949
00:56:25,317 --> 00:56:26,985
I just thought you should know.

950
00:56:27,027 --> 00:56:30,197
Jeez, I'm in a state of shock here.
I can hardly speak.

951
00:56:30,239 --> 00:56:33,408
There was a car accident,
a terrible car accident.

952
00:56:33,450 --> 00:56:36,870
Mike Prince, Henry,
driving to the poker game.

953
00:56:36,954 --> 00:56:39,665
Head-on collision with another car.
Two girls dead. Henry's dead.

954
00:56:39,748 --> 00:56:41,083
Mike's in a coma.

955
00:56:41,250 --> 00:56:43,502
Even a pedestrian on the pavement
is on the critical list.

956
00:56:43,710 --> 00:56:45,003
It's just unbelievable.

957
00:56:45,087 --> 00:56:48,674
Two teenage drunks nicked the car...
Bam! Unbelievable.

958
00:56:52,761 --> 00:56:55,180
He couldn't get his mind around it.

959
00:56:55,514 --> 00:56:58,976
Mike Prince in a coma? A vegetable?

960
00:56:59,017 --> 00:57:01,061
Henry Strangler gone.

961
00:57:01,854 --> 00:57:03,230
He wasn't even that close with them,

962
00:57:03,313 --> 00:57:07,359
but it made him feel
how quick and fragile is existence.

963
00:57:10,487 --> 00:57:13,198
And that's when he had his crazy thought.

964
00:57:23,083 --> 00:57:25,002
Strangler lived alone.

965
00:57:25,085 --> 00:57:28,130
He had no family,
no time for a woman in his life,

966
00:57:28,130 --> 00:57:31,383
and was obsessively private
about his first novel.

967
00:57:31,383 --> 00:57:35,846
Roy was the only one he'd trusted to read it,
this Roy knew for sure.

968
00:57:36,972 --> 00:57:41,018
Strangler had just finished tweaking it
and had not shown it to Malcolm Dodds yet

969
00:57:41,143 --> 00:57:43,437
because Roy was to arrange that.

970
00:57:43,437 --> 00:57:45,022
Strangler had no agent

971
00:57:45,314 --> 00:57:47,024
and none of the other poker players
were writers,

972
00:57:47,191 --> 00:57:51,028
and so had no particular interest in
or knowledge of his progress.

973
00:57:52,196 --> 00:57:56,116
The man was a drone,
a perfectionist, a workaholic.

974
00:57:56,950 --> 00:58:00,662
Possibly a genius
who'd written a terrific first book,

975
00:58:01,163 --> 00:58:03,916
but tragically and most conveniently,

976
00:58:05,083 --> 00:58:06,418
he was dead.

977
00:58:32,903 --> 00:58:34,196
I'm not familiar with your shop,

978
00:58:34,279 --> 00:58:36,782
but I'll make it my business
to tell Cristal all about it.

979
00:58:36,907 --> 00:58:41,370
Well, it's only small, but I think we carry
most of the important occult books.

980
00:58:41,537 --> 00:58:44,665
-Do you have any literature on reincarnation?
-Yes.

981
00:58:44,790 --> 00:58:48,335
You know, sometimes I get a clear flash
that I've visited a place before.

982
00:58:48,418 --> 00:58:49,878
Perhaps ancient Egypt.

983
00:58:50,128 --> 00:58:51,922
My son-in-law pooh-poohs it,

984
00:58:52,172 --> 00:58:54,967
but if I didn't think there was more to life,
I couldn't go on.

985
00:58:55,050 --> 00:58:58,595
You'd have got on well
with my dear, departed Claire.

986
00:58:59,847 --> 00:59:03,934
I've tried unsuccessfully to contact her
so far, but I won't give up.

987
00:59:04,351 --> 00:59:06,979
You obviously cared for her very deeply.

988
00:59:07,604 --> 00:59:10,232
Yes, it's been very lonely without her.

989
00:59:11,817 --> 00:59:14,987
It's got quite a bit of a kick to it.
It's got some chili oil in it.

990
00:59:15,070 --> 00:59:18,782
Hey, come on, get dressed.
We're meeting the Hoveys in 45 minutes.

991
00:59:20,284 --> 00:59:21,827
What are you doing?

992
00:59:21,910 --> 00:59:23,912
Come on. Get dressed.
We're meeting the Hoveys.

993
00:59:24,538 --> 00:59:27,082
I don't feel like seeing
one of them boring plays again.

994
00:59:27,082 --> 00:59:28,876
Well, this'll be great. Come on.

995
00:59:29,001 --> 00:59:32,713
That's what you said about the one Friday
and it was so boring.

996
00:59:33,172 --> 00:59:36,049
It was! Weren't even scary.

997
00:59:36,175 --> 00:59:38,427
Well, the ghosts were meant to be symbolic.

998
00:59:38,552 --> 00:59:41,346
It wasn't intended to be a scary play,
you know?

999
00:59:43,223 --> 00:59:47,686
Come on, look, it's not that I don't like
being at home with you, believe me.

1000
00:59:47,978 --> 00:59:51,315
It's too quiet in this house.
It's like a freaking echo.

1001
00:59:51,815 --> 00:59:54,526
You never like watching any of the telly I like.

1002
00:59:54,610 --> 00:59:57,488
Okay, well, I don't know.
What the hell are we talking about here?

1003
00:59:58,906 --> 01:00:04,036
What?

1004
01:00:05,078 --> 01:00:07,998
I'd like to do more things I like
once in a while.

1005
01:00:08,081 --> 01:00:10,542
Okay, all right. The rest of the week,
we'll do what you want.

1006
01:00:10,542 --> 01:00:12,252
Is that okay? Okay?

1007
01:00:12,961 --> 01:00:16,882
Come to the show tonight, and we'll do...
You call the shots the rest of the week.

1008
01:00:16,965 --> 01:00:18,550
How about that?

1009
01:00:23,138 --> 01:00:25,015
This is banging, isn't it?

1010
01:00:25,516 --> 01:00:27,017
I love this tune.

1011
01:00:37,069 --> 01:00:39,321
-Alfie, can I have a dance with him?
-What?

1012
01:00:39,488 --> 01:00:41,907
Can I dance with him? It's boring just sitting.

1013
01:00:42,032 --> 01:00:43,033
Yes?

1014
01:00:43,116 --> 01:00:46,286
-Okay. Don't stay out there too long.
-I won't.

1015
01:01:13,147 --> 01:01:16,191
Sally announced to Roy
she was starting her own gallery

1016
01:01:16,191 --> 01:01:18,318
and the time had come for a divorce.

1017
01:01:18,485 --> 01:01:23,323
By now, Dia had strong romantic ideas
about sharing her life with a writer.

1018
01:01:23,866 --> 01:01:26,952
-Your book is really riveting.
-Thank you.

1019
01:01:27,077 --> 01:01:31,206
You obviously must have spent
a lot of time in Ireland and Scotland.

1020
01:01:32,583 --> 01:01:36,086
Some. I did a lot of research.
A lot of research.

1021
01:01:36,170 --> 01:01:39,256
I thought you told me
you've never been to Ireland.

1022
01:01:39,882 --> 01:01:43,051
Northern Ireland.
But I've been to other places.

1023
01:01:43,135 --> 01:01:45,846
I've been to Connemara.
That's one of the places I've been.

1024
01:01:46,096 --> 01:01:49,433
I loved so much the style of your writing,
you know?

1025
01:01:49,433 --> 01:01:51,894
Each word clicks along the page,

1026
01:01:52,019 --> 01:01:57,858
and your characters are so rich
and almost startling.

1027
01:01:57,983 --> 01:02:00,736
Wow. Thank you.
That's a huge compliment, coming from you.

1028
01:02:00,777 --> 01:02:01,904
-Thank you so much.
-No, no. It's all right.

1029
01:02:01,904 --> 01:02:04,072
It is. He hardly likes anything, believe me.

1030
01:02:04,239 --> 01:02:05,741
How's Alan, sweetheart?

1031
01:02:05,908 --> 01:02:08,285
-He's good, Mom.
-Is he coming this weekend?

1032
01:02:08,952 --> 01:02:10,704
Your father is very encouraging.

1033
01:02:10,746 --> 01:02:12,581
And he's a lovely guy.

1034
01:02:12,581 --> 01:02:14,750
Well, he's not that lovely
when he doesn't like something.

1035
01:02:14,833 --> 01:02:16,001
No?

1036
01:02:16,043 --> 01:02:19,046
He's written a lot of criticism
for small literary magazines

1037
01:02:19,171 --> 01:02:21,256
and nothing much impresses him.

1038
01:02:22,549 --> 01:02:25,636
Well, what can I say? You're my muse.

1039
01:02:25,636 --> 01:02:28,430
You popped into my life
just when I needed divine inspiration.

1040
01:02:28,430 --> 01:02:29,848
It's amazing.

1041
01:02:29,973 --> 01:02:33,060
-Well, that's what a muse does, right?
-I guess so.

1042
01:02:35,354 --> 01:02:37,648
-I love it here.
-It's lovely weather.

1043
01:02:47,074 --> 01:02:48,951
I don't even want to think what I'm thinking.

1044
01:02:49,076 --> 01:02:51,078
I can think of nothing else.

1045
01:02:52,621 --> 01:02:54,498
What am I going to do?

1046
01:02:55,707 --> 01:02:57,376
What I want you to do?

1047
01:02:58,252 --> 01:03:01,839
I want you as my forever muse.

1048
01:03:02,381 --> 01:03:06,552
Here, or in Paris. I write,
we open wine bottles, we make love.

1049
01:03:07,052 --> 01:03:11,849
They're all en route for the wedding.
Alan's family, his relatives and our friends.

1050
01:03:13,058 --> 01:03:15,352
Alan's going to be devastated.

1051
01:03:22,234 --> 01:03:23,485
That's okay.

1052
01:03:24,319 --> 01:03:25,737
It's so wrong.

1053
01:03:28,615 --> 01:03:31,118
Look, I've told you before
not to make any large purchase

1054
01:03:31,160 --> 01:03:32,828
without consulting me first.

1055
01:03:33,412 --> 01:03:34,746
But you said I could have them both.

1056
01:03:34,830 --> 01:03:37,624
That was a while ago.
The picture's changed now.

1057
01:03:37,708 --> 01:03:39,084
Did you go bust or something?

1058
01:03:39,209 --> 01:03:43,630
God, I've tried to explain to you,
at this point in time, cash is tight.

1059
01:03:43,630 --> 01:03:47,551
I lost a lot in the stock market
and Helena won't budge on the alimony.

1060
01:03:47,634 --> 01:03:51,013
We have to be more budget conscious,
that's all I'm saying.

1061
01:03:52,806 --> 01:03:54,183
Hey, come here.

1062
01:03:55,517 --> 01:03:58,353
You know how much I like to pamper you
and get you nice things.

1063
01:03:58,353 --> 01:04:02,274
But just ask me
before you spend this kind of money,

1064
01:04:02,316 --> 01:04:05,152
until I catch up on some expenditure, okay?

1065
01:04:06,111 --> 01:04:08,739
-I'm sorry.
-Yeah, I am, too, if I yelled.

1066
01:04:10,657 --> 01:04:15,412
Your face is all red.
You've got to watch your blood pressure.

1067
01:04:15,579 --> 01:04:16,914
Remember what the doctor said.

1068
01:04:16,955 --> 01:04:20,667
He says I've got
the arteries of a man half my age.

1069
01:04:20,792 --> 01:04:24,213
You know, I just have to get
to the gym more often to exercise.

1070
01:04:24,213 --> 01:04:29,885
I'm just working so hard. Yeah.
Hey, coat looks beautiful.

1071
01:04:30,052 --> 01:04:31,345
Fantastic.

1072
01:04:32,846 --> 01:04:36,141
The truth was that business reverses
and Alfie's extravagance

1073
01:04:36,183 --> 01:04:38,685
had led him into serious financial trouble.

1074
01:04:38,769 --> 01:04:43,315
And while he tried to keep up appearances,
he had become over his head in debt.

1075
01:04:58,413 --> 01:05:00,165
Your back any better?

1076
01:05:00,833 --> 01:05:01,917
What?

1077
01:05:02,376 --> 01:05:03,961
I said, your back any better?

1078
01:05:04,044 --> 01:05:06,213
Yeah. I've done my leg in now.

1079
01:05:07,631 --> 01:05:10,050
I think I overdid the pedaling
when you weren't around.

1080
01:05:10,050 --> 01:05:13,053
Well, I should come around more often.
Let me have a look.

1081
01:05:13,136 --> 01:05:15,264
You probably sprained it or something.

1082
01:05:15,305 --> 01:05:16,515
Come on.

1083
01:05:23,313 --> 01:05:25,065
You do have the touch.

1084
01:05:25,399 --> 01:05:27,734
I should be paying you,
not the other way around.

1085
01:05:28,902 --> 01:05:30,612
I'm very expensive.

1086
01:05:33,365 --> 01:05:37,119
You know, there's a rumor
that before you married Alfie Shepridge

1087
01:05:37,369 --> 01:05:39,204
that you worked in Las Vegas.

1088
01:05:39,371 --> 01:05:40,873
-Is that so?
-Yeah.

1089
01:05:41,123 --> 01:05:43,041
Were you in a show there?

1090
01:05:43,125 --> 01:05:45,419
Someone said a cocktail waitress.

1091
01:05:46,044 --> 01:05:48,380
But I reckon you were a model.

1092
01:05:50,465 --> 01:05:55,888
Whatever it was I did,
you can bet I was pretty good.

1093
01:05:57,181 --> 01:05:59,349
You must have enjoyed your work.

1094
01:05:59,516 --> 01:06:01,101
Well, why wouldn't I?

1095
01:06:02,060 --> 01:06:04,480
On the other hand, if you liked it so much,

1096
01:06:05,731 --> 01:06:09,651
maybe you wouldn't have retired
and married Alfie Shepridge.

1097
01:06:10,944 --> 01:06:14,031
Well, if I said with some,
it wasn't always great.

1098
01:06:15,616 --> 01:06:19,244
But with most of the men I met,
it was very stimulating.

1099
01:06:21,163 --> 01:06:24,041
In what way was it stimulating?

1100
01:06:25,000 --> 01:06:26,919
I learned a lot of things.

1101
01:06:28,837 --> 01:06:32,132
I met some very handsome actors
who liked to party.

1102
01:06:32,216 --> 01:06:35,469
Some footballers who were pretty athletic.

1103
01:06:35,802 --> 01:06:37,471
What'd they teach you?

1104
01:06:38,180 --> 01:06:40,516
Let's say we taught each other.

1105
01:06:43,060 --> 01:06:44,812
You want to teach me?

1106
01:06:50,818 --> 01:06:51,985
Not here.

1107
01:06:54,905 --> 01:06:56,156
I'm not yelling!

1108
01:06:56,240 --> 01:06:58,575
Christ, can you blame me for being upset?

1109
01:06:58,575 --> 01:07:01,078
Of course he's upset.
Do you know what you're doing?

1110
01:07:01,286 --> 01:07:03,413
Can you all control yourselves, please?

1111
01:07:03,539 --> 01:07:07,042
We've got 1 23 people to notify.
Some of them have already flown in.

1112
01:07:07,084 --> 01:07:10,170
They're coming from Europe,
from Spain and Lugano.

1113
01:07:10,254 --> 01:07:13,048
Yes, I know that. I know that.

1114
01:07:13,048 --> 01:07:15,217
-Have you met someone else?
-What about the caterers, the band?

1115
01:07:15,259 --> 01:07:17,094
-This is not the time to discuss...
-Have you met someone else?

1116
01:07:17,219 --> 01:07:19,096
The band is getting on a plane
right now from India!

1117
01:07:19,096 --> 01:07:21,265
-Do you know how much this is gonna cost?
-Yes.

1118
01:07:21,431 --> 01:07:22,474
-She's met somebody else?
-Yes, I did.

1119
01:07:22,641 --> 01:07:25,519
-What?
-Who is he? Where did you meet him?

1120
01:07:25,686 --> 01:07:26,687
I don't want to talk about it!

1121
01:07:26,687 --> 01:07:29,148
Tarak, please! She's met someone else!

1122
01:07:29,189 --> 01:07:31,024
-She's met someone else?
-She's met someone else.

1123
01:07:31,150 --> 01:07:33,569
-When?
-I can't believe this is happening.

1124
01:07:33,569 --> 01:07:35,571
-Stupid. She's stupid.
-I cannot believe it.

1125
01:07:36,780 --> 01:07:38,365
Well, I guess if you can
fall in love so quickly,

1126
01:07:38,448 --> 01:07:40,868
-it's probably good we found out now.
-It's not that I don't care about you.

1127
01:07:41,034 --> 01:07:42,452
-Don't give me that!
-I'm really sorry. I feel awful.

1128
01:07:42,578 --> 01:07:44,371
-I didn't plan this.
-We had so many plans.

1129
01:07:44,413 --> 01:07:47,708
-I hate you. I hate you!
-Becky, that's enough.

1130
01:07:47,791 --> 01:07:50,419
Excuse me, don't you shout at my daughter.
That's my job.

1131
01:07:50,419 --> 01:07:51,712
Excuse me?

1132
01:07:51,879 --> 01:07:54,256
-How could she do this to my brother?
-Becky, Becky, calm down.

1133
01:07:54,339 --> 01:07:56,675
Can we all just calm down?

1134
01:07:56,717 --> 01:07:58,552
It's so disrespectful!

1135
01:07:58,677 --> 01:07:59,720
Calm down!

1136
01:08:06,018 --> 01:08:07,811
There you are, darling.

1137
01:08:08,604 --> 01:08:11,982
Do you recognize this?
We've passed here a million times.

1138
01:08:12,483 --> 01:08:14,776
I haven't seen you so perky in ages, Mum.

1139
01:08:14,902 --> 01:08:17,779
He's a very spiritual man.
We have a lot to talk about.

1140
01:08:17,779 --> 01:08:21,241
Cristal says it has positive future potential.
Come on.

1141
01:08:23,827 --> 01:08:26,705
There's a nice old pub on the corner.
Let me go and close up.

1142
01:08:26,788 --> 01:08:27,789
Good.

1143
01:08:27,831 --> 01:08:31,460
Has your mother told you
I've grown very fond of her?

1144
01:08:38,342 --> 01:08:40,719
Isn't he the most interesting man?

1145
01:08:41,512 --> 01:08:43,889
I'm just so glad you found somebody.

1146
01:08:43,889 --> 01:08:48,143
Well, he may not be a tall, dark stranger,
but he's become my stranger.

1147
01:08:48,393 --> 01:08:51,980
Mum, you always said that if I needed
a loan to start my own business,

1148
01:08:51,980 --> 01:08:53,148
I could count on you.

1149
01:08:53,982 --> 01:08:56,693
And, well, there's nowhere else I can go.

1150
01:08:56,819 --> 01:08:58,654
To open your own gallery? Of course.

1151
01:08:58,779 --> 01:09:00,447
Cristal said you've got
a new future ahead of you,

1152
01:09:00,781 --> 01:09:02,449
now you're rid of that albatross.

1153
01:09:02,533 --> 01:09:05,452
Yes. I want to start over.

1154
01:09:06,787 --> 01:09:09,248
What about that exciting man you work for?

1155
01:09:09,289 --> 01:09:11,792
I know, you said he was married,

1156
01:09:11,917 --> 01:09:14,545
but I seem to recall
you did say there were problems.

1157
01:09:14,586 --> 01:09:18,757
Well, I wish I could say that
I left Roy for Greg, but no such luck.

1158
01:09:18,882 --> 01:09:21,718
Don't be defeatist.
I knew you were wild about him.

1159
01:09:21,718 --> 01:09:23,720
I asked Cristal about it.

1160
01:09:24,346 --> 01:09:26,682
She said she got the distinct impression

1161
01:09:26,807 --> 01:09:28,934
that you ought to make
your feelings known to him.

1162
01:09:29,017 --> 01:09:32,187
Well, I think he knew. I think.

1163
01:09:35,357 --> 01:09:39,862
You know, Sally, I'm very sorry
to hear you'll be leaving.

1164
01:09:39,987 --> 01:09:42,614
But at the same time,

1165
01:09:44,491 --> 01:09:46,785
you know, I wish you only the best.

1166
01:09:47,494 --> 01:09:50,581
Because you actually deserve it.

1167
01:09:51,790 --> 01:09:55,252
I really appreciate all the experience here.

1168
01:09:56,128 --> 01:09:59,548
You know, of all of my assistants,

1169
01:10:00,174 --> 01:10:03,260
I enjoyed working with you
the most, actually.

1170
01:10:05,512 --> 01:10:06,722
In truth,

1171
01:10:08,015 --> 01:10:11,643
I think I was beginning to grow

1172
01:10:11,810 --> 01:10:14,980
maybe a little too fond
of the time we spent together.

1173
01:10:16,356 --> 01:10:20,068
Well, we had very much
the same artistic tastes.

1174
01:10:20,402 --> 01:10:23,614
And I'm sure that had become very obvious.

1175
01:10:23,947 --> 01:10:25,157
What had?

1176
01:10:26,617 --> 01:10:30,913
That I was starting to feel
a little too close to you.

1177
01:10:31,121 --> 01:10:32,789
Not at all.

1178
