1416
01:25:42,616 --> 01:25:45,828
I'm sorry. Is there anything I can do?

1417
01:25:46,578 --> 01:25:47,412
No.

1418
01:25:49,248 --> 01:25:53,252
Well, Mum, Cristal always seems to know
what's best for you.

1419
01:25:53,335 --> 01:25:56,213
And if she says the future looks good,
you can bet on it.

1420
01:25:56,296 --> 01:26:00,259
Another life.
I just have to shed the old one and try again.

1421
01:26:03,303 --> 01:26:08,392
Mum, I know I told you
about a substantial loan I'd need

1422
01:26:08,392 --> 01:26:10,018
to get the art gallery started up,

1423
01:26:10,018 --> 01:26:14,148
but, well, it turns out
it's a bit more than I anticipated.

1424
01:26:15,149 --> 01:26:16,358
Not a lot.

1425
01:26:16,400 --> 01:26:18,652
And it'll all come back to you,

1426
01:26:18,986 --> 01:26:21,155
but maybe not for a year or two.

1427
01:26:22,614 --> 01:26:26,201
About the loan, darling,
the timing right now is wrong.

1428
01:26:26,243 --> 01:26:28,787
With interest, of course. What?

1429
01:26:29,621 --> 01:26:30,998
The aspects are not right.

1430
01:26:31,915 --> 01:26:33,709
What are you talking about? What aspects?

1431
01:26:33,709 --> 01:26:37,462
I spoke to Cristal, and she said I can't do it

1432
01:26:37,546 --> 01:26:40,299
because the stars
are not in the right alignment.

1433
01:26:41,049 --> 01:26:42,426
What?

1434
01:26:42,676 --> 01:26:45,345
Cristal said the planets tell her

1435
01:26:47,014 --> 01:26:51,810
I must not enter into any financial
transactions for the indefinite future.

1436
01:26:52,186 --> 01:26:54,563
And certainly the loan
comes under that heading.

1437
01:26:54,646 --> 01:26:57,024
Mother, she doesn't know
what she's talking about.

1438
01:26:57,232 --> 01:27:00,152
-Sally.
-Mother, I was counting on that money!

1439
01:27:00,194 --> 01:27:04,198
Someday, perhaps, but not with
the planets in their present conjunction.

1440
01:27:04,239 --> 01:27:06,992
Cristal doesn't know
what she's talking about!

1441
01:27:07,034 --> 01:27:09,953
-Please.
-She's a charlatan!

1442
01:27:10,287 --> 01:27:12,456
We're talking about Cristal Delgiorno.

1443
01:27:12,539 --> 01:27:14,666
I need that loan!

1444
01:27:14,666 --> 01:27:18,253
-Cristal said...
-I don't care what Cristal said!

1445
01:27:18,462 --> 01:27:19,880
I can't!

1446
01:27:20,047 --> 01:27:21,673
She's a fraud!

1447
01:27:23,383 --> 01:27:24,885
Do you hear what you're saying?

1448
01:27:25,010 --> 01:27:27,346
She's a fake fortune teller!

1449
01:27:27,513 --> 01:27:30,808
There's no such thing
as predicting the future!

1450
01:27:30,808 --> 01:27:32,309
Are you mad?

1451
01:27:32,351 --> 01:27:35,187
You've always been her greatest supporter.

1452
01:27:35,687 --> 01:27:38,482
I was only saying those things
just to keep you happy,

1453
01:27:38,649 --> 01:27:40,025
to keep you from harming yourself!

1454
01:27:40,150 --> 01:27:42,611
She's a blatant, conniving little fraud!

1455
01:27:42,653 --> 01:27:44,363
You sound like your ex.

1456
01:27:44,613 --> 01:27:49,409
Darling, I know you've been through
the most horrible breakup.

1457
01:27:49,993 --> 01:27:52,120
I have to have that money.

1458
01:27:52,204 --> 01:27:53,121
Not now.

1459
01:27:53,747 --> 01:27:55,290
Cristal says no.

1460
01:27:56,333 --> 01:27:59,586
You idiot! You poor, pathetic,
gullible imbecile!

1461
01:27:59,711 --> 01:28:02,548
Don't you see? She just tells you
what you want to hear,

1462
01:28:02,631 --> 01:28:04,508
and then robs you of your money!

1463
01:28:04,925 --> 01:28:07,344
Darling, if I give you the money now,

1464
01:28:07,386 --> 01:28:10,389
it would be bad luck, she said,
for you as well as me.

1465
01:28:10,556 --> 01:28:12,349
You crazy imbecile!

1466
01:28:12,558 --> 01:28:14,977
I need that loan, you lunatic!

1467
01:28:15,018 --> 01:28:17,271
I'm doing this for your own good.

1468
01:28:18,188 --> 01:28:20,607
Cristal has the power of prophecy.

1469
01:28:23,402 --> 01:28:25,821
Come on, Henry, wake up, mate.
We know you're faking it.

1470
01:28:25,904 --> 01:28:28,615
We really miss you at the poker game, Henry.

1471
01:28:29,408 --> 01:28:32,286
We found a really nice girl for you,
didn't we, lads?

1472
01:28:32,411 --> 01:28:35,873
She's right up your street,
she's got the overbite and everything.

1473
01:28:36,248 --> 01:28:38,250
Are you hearing us, Henry?

1474
01:28:38,750 --> 01:28:40,711
I know you can hear us.

1475
01:28:41,253 --> 01:28:45,090
If you can understand us, wiggle your fingers

1476
01:28:46,258 --> 01:28:48,719
or make a fist.

1477
01:28:48,719 --> 01:28:51,388
Blink. We'll take anything, right, Roy?

1478
01:28:52,014 --> 01:28:53,891
Listen, Roy's written a book.

1479
01:28:54,016 --> 01:28:55,893
It's about a child pornographer in Belfast.

1480
01:28:56,018 --> 01:28:58,812
You want to get yourself well to read it.
It's got bestseller written all over it.

1481
01:28:58,854 --> 01:29:00,355
He's blinking.

1482
01:29:00,397 --> 01:29:02,524
Is he blinking? I can't tell.

1483
01:29:03,317 --> 01:29:05,819
Blink twice if you understand me, Henry.

1484
01:29:05,819 --> 01:29:08,822
The doctor said he was optimistic.
Talk to him, Roy.

1485
01:29:08,906 --> 01:29:11,992
Blink if you can hear us, Henry.
Can you hear us?

1486
01:29:14,119 --> 01:29:18,165
He's blinking. It's very faint.
Do it again! See?

1487
01:29:18,332 --> 01:29:20,751
-He understands. He definitely understands.
-There.

1488
01:29:20,834 --> 01:29:24,129
That head neurologist said it all had to do
with the portion of the brain affected.

1489
01:29:24,129 --> 01:29:26,256
He's convinced
Henry's going to come out of it.

1490
01:29:26,381 --> 01:29:27,591
That'd be marvelous.

1491
01:29:27,591 --> 01:29:29,009
Hey, if you've got the time,

1492
01:29:29,009 --> 01:29:30,552
you should come in
and read him your new book.

1493
01:29:30,552 --> 01:29:32,554
-Henry.
-I know he can understand.

1494
01:29:32,554 --> 01:29:35,224
-Henry!
-Do it again, Henry. Blink again!

1495
01:29:50,531 --> 01:29:53,867
I contacted Claire, put the question to her,

1496
01:29:53,909 --> 01:29:55,911
and she said there'd be no problem

1497
01:29:55,911 --> 01:29:58,372
if you were to become
the second Mrs. Wunch.

1498
01:29:58,539 --> 01:29:59,456
She said that?

1499
01:29:59,581 --> 01:30:03,710
She rapped twice for no when I asked
if she'd mind if I married you.

1500
01:30:03,752 --> 01:30:05,712
You always said
she was an understanding woman.

1501
01:30:05,796 --> 01:30:08,465
I'm not sure she didn't exist once as royalty.

1502
01:30:08,882 --> 01:30:11,760
It's so comforting to know
we live over and over again.

1503
01:30:11,802 --> 01:30:14,388
If only I could convince Alfie,
he'd be so much happier.

1504
01:30:14,513 --> 01:30:15,430
Yes.

1505
01:30:15,514 --> 01:30:19,768
It's time to close the book on our little tale
of sound and fury, signifying nothing.

1506
01:30:20,978 --> 01:30:25,983
And one has to wonder,
given all of life's uncertainty and pain,

1507
01:30:26,024 --> 01:30:27,985
how do we get through it?

1508
01:30:28,026 --> 01:30:30,612
Well, as Sally told Roy,

1509
01:30:30,737 --> 01:30:33,699
sometimes the illusions
work better than the medicine.

1510
01:30:33,866 --> 01:30:36,910
I was a peasant, just a simple peasant,

1511
01:30:36,952 --> 01:30:41,039
but you, you were something very special.

1512
01:30:41,748 --> 01:30:46,545
Sometimes my intuition makes me think
that you might have lived before

1513
01:30:46,587 --> 01:30:48,964
as Cleopatra or Joan of Arc.

1514
01:30:50,382 --> 01:30:53,385
Cristal Delgiorno's confirmed
that I lived before,

1515
01:30:53,385 --> 01:30:56,555
and I've always had a particular fondness
for everything French.

1516
01:30:56,555 --> 01:31:00,225
So, I'm inclined to think
you may be right about Joan of Arc.

1517
01:31:00,559 --> 01:31:02,644
Sometimes I have memories of my past lives.

1518
01:31:02,728 --> 01:31:04,104
Do you?

1519
01:31:04,188 --> 01:31:06,607
I do. Yes.

1520
01:31:06,648 --> 01:31:08,025
In France.

